<!--
    Brazilian Portuguese (pt-rBR).
    Android uses the region qualifier "rBR" to distinguish this variant from
    European Portuguese (values-pt/).  When a device is set to pt-BR, Android
    resolves resources in this order: values-pt-rBR → values-pt → values/.
    Therefore only strings that actually differ from European Portuguese need
    to be listed here; Android will fall back to values-pt/ for the rest.
    However, to keep the file self-contained and to make future maintenance
    easier, all 175 strings are included.

    Key differences from European Portuguese (pt):
      • "Definições" → "Configurações"  (settings)
      • "Registos"   → "Registros"      (entries – EP uses -os)
      • "Guardar"    → "Salvar"         (save)
      • "Eliminar"   → "Excluir"        (delete)
      • "Ficheiro"   → "Arquivo"        (file)
      • "Transferências" → "Downloads"  (download folder)
      • "Teor alcoólico" → "Teor alcoólico" (same, kept)
      • Informal "você" register replaces EP "toque"/"selecione" imperatives
        with the equivalent Brazilian forms.
-->
